China's vehicle sales will total about 28.1 million units this year, flat with the 2018 level, according to a report jointly released by the China Association of Automobile Manufacturers.Sales of passenger vehicles will be about 23.7 million units, similar to last year.Sales of new-energy vehicles (NEVs) may rise about 27 percent to 1.6 million, the report said.Although auto sales in China fell 2.8 percent to 28.08 million units last year, the country still accounted for 30.6 percent of the global market, the report said.As of the end of last year, China had been the world's largest auto market for 10 consecutive years.NEV sales jumped by 61.7 percent last year to 1.26 million units on the back of favorable government policies, representing 60 percent of global NEV sales, the report said.China will improve the market environment for car sales and expand the supply of automobiles as part of its efforts to boost auto consumption.The country will strengthen law enforcement to crack down on irregular operations by car dealers so that consumers can make purchases in a market with orderly competition, Gao Feng, the spokesperson for the Ministry of Commerce, said at a press conference on April 4.The ministry will also work with other government agencies to expand the supply of automobiles to meet more diversified demand, Gao said.Car manufacturers operating in China have slashed the sticker prices of cars in recent weeks after China announced cuts in value-added tax rates in manufacturing and other industries.The VAT cuts will boost auto consumption, while allowing car manufacturers to invest more into upgrading their products, Gao said. Chinese scientists design gene-editing tool using light to kill cancer cellsAbsence at PLA maritime parade will prevent US from learning about Chinese Navy: expertsChinese American organization condemns increasing racial profiling in US Utah celebrates 150th birthday of Transcontinental RailroadActress Liu honored with Hollywood Walk of Fame star